# AI Developer Workflows (ADW) Configuration for Mochi Donut
# ============================================================

# Mode A: Claude Max Subscription (Default - Recommended for Interactive Use)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If you have a Claude Max subscription, no configuration is needed!
# Claude Code will authenticate through your subscription automatically.
# This is the easiest way to use ADWs for interactive development.
#
# Advantages:
# - No API key management needed
# - Works immediately out of the box
# - Perfect for local development
#
# Limitations:
# - User must be logged in to Claude
# - Not suitable for fully automated/headless workflows
# - Cannot run in CI/CD without additional setup


# Mode B: API-Based Programmatic Execution (For Automation & CI/CD)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# For headless automation, CI/CD pipelines, or server-side execution,
# you'll need an Anthropic API key.
#
# Uncomment and set your API key:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# Use cases:
# - CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions, etc.)
# - Webhook-triggered workflows
# - Scheduled tasks (cron jobs)
# - Server-side automation
#
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys


# Optional: Claude Code CLI Path
# -------------------------------
# If Claude Code is not in your PATH, specify its location:
# CLAUDE_CODE_PATH=/usr/local/bin/claude
#
# The system will auto-detect Claude in common locations:
# - ~/.claude/local/claude
# - /usr/local/bin/claude
# - /opt/homebrew/bin/claude
# - /usr/bin/claude


# Optional: Working Directory Behavior
# -------------------------------------
# Maintain project working directory across Bash commands:
# CLAUDE_BASH_MAINTAIN_PROJECT_WORKING_DIR=true
